Come Thru has problematic lyrics. The man is basically blackmailing the girl to "come thru" or else he'll tell her man. First of all, that's male entitlement right there. Male entitlement is basically when a man feels like a woman owes him something because he has done this and that for that woman, this robs the woman of her independence, a woman doesn't owe that man anything just because the man feels something for her. Second, it's not "just a song" problematic ideas like this manifested in pop culture contributes to the problem. Please be mindful next time when writing lyrics and don't take things like these lightly. As a last note, I'll quote: "Women should have the unequivocal right to say no. Women should have absolute dominion over their own bodies. Women should not, as I have so many times, apologize for rejecting a man." In case you wanna read more please see: https://thebodyisnotanapology.com/magazine/we-belong-to-ourselves-on-male-entitlement-and-womens-right-to-say-no/  Thanks for listening.
